  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare functional and anatomical results of a combined
      surgery and two time surgery for macular hole and cataract extraction in one hundred and
      twenty patients (120 eyes) with idiopathic Macular Hole (MH) and cataract in two academic
      centers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Main outcome measures were the assessment of visual acuity at 6 and 12 months,and the rate of
      closure of MH by OCT (optical coherence tomography).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
